cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM 

This paper deals with computer vision applications, specifically domain adaptation, few shot learning, and zero-shot learning. These topics are typically covered in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of semantic attributes, which falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Finally, the experiments involve benchmark datasets, which could fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
